					<description><![CDATA[<p>SpectronRx has announced that it has raised $85 million in funding from the New York private investment group OrbiMed. The injection of funding will be used for the gigantic expansion</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/spectronrx-secures-85m-for-radiopharmaceutical-growth/" data-wpel-link="internal">SpectronRx Secures $85M for Radiopharmaceutical Growth</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.spectronrx.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">SpectronRx </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has announced that it has raised $85 million in </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/moonbounce-raises-12m-to-power-real%e2%80%91time-ai-control/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">from the New York private investment group OrbiMed. The injection of funding will be used for the gigantic expansion of the company&#8217;s MedIsotope manufacturing and contract manufacturing capacity in the face of the worldwide bottleneck in cancer-treating radioligand therapies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The investment comes at a crucial juncture for the industry. </span>Smart bombs for cancer drugs to tumour cells have surged in clinical success, but infrastructure for isotopes is slow. SpectronRx&#8217;s fresh injection is intended to address this supply chain crunch at its hub in Bunker Hill, Indiana, by expanding.</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Building a &#8220;One-Stop Shop&#8221; for Radiomedicine</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">SpectronRx has established a dual-threat play in the form of its CDMO/prime isotope provider status. </span>The combination of these two traditionally separated halves of the business is designed to eliminate logistical ping-pong, delaying drug launches.</p>
<div id="attachment_199675" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-199675" class="size-large wp-image-199675" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/SpectronRx-1-1024x307.png" alt="SpectronRx" width="1024" height="307" /><p id="caption-attachment-199675" class="wp-caption-text">Source: SpectronRx</p></div>
<p>&#8220;While radiopharmaceutical innovation is progressing swiftly, access to isotopes and manufacturing capacity remain the major bottlenecks,&#8221; said John Zehner. The company&#8217;s range of high-purity isotopes is comprehensive, extending from diagnostic essentials such as Technetium-99 to Actinium-225.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News</span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/moonbounce-raises-12m-to-power-real%e2%80%91time-ai-control/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">: Moonbounce Raises $12M to Power Real‑Time AI Control</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Massive Physical Footprint</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Most of the $85 million will go toward specialized equipment and steel. </span>The company&#8217;s 34-acre Grissom Aeroplex campus has been expanded with a new 150,000 square foot production building. Zehner states the complex can produce over 300,000 patient doses annually, with design configurable beyond a million square feet.</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Economic Impact and Strategic Location</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This expansion is not only a victory for oncology; it is also a significant boost for the Indiana economy. SpectronRx estimates the growth has the potential to generate as many as 100 new high-tech jobs within the next two years.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The decision to locate at the Grissom Aeroplex is no accident. Few industries rely so heavily on logistics as radiopharmaceuticals, whose short half-lives (some lose half their activity within hours) demand a relentless focus on transportation. The Aeroplex is served by a 24/7 general aviation airport and is within a 12-hour drive of 60% of the population.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Easy access to high-quality medical isotopes is a critical requirement to enable the development of the next generation of precision diagnostics,&#8221; commented Lars Enstrom, Managing Director of OrbiMed. &#8220;SpectronRx has a platform that will enable the company to become an integral part of this growth.&#8221;</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/spectronrx-secures-85m-for-radiopharmaceutical-growth/" data-wpel-link="internal">SpectronRx Secures $85M for Radiopharmaceutical Growth</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
